WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.696
Our beautiful homeland,

00:00:06.763 --> 00:00:12.775
O so fearless and gracious.

00:00:13.862 --> 00:00:18.200
Our fathers’ ancient glory,

00:00:20.672 --> 00:00:25.639
May you be blessed forever.

00:00:28.056 --> 00:00:32.024
Dear, you are our only glory,

00:00:34.514 --> 00:00:37.754
Dear, you are our only one,

00:00:41.718 --> 00:00:45.876
Dear, we love your plains,

00:00:48.624 --> 00:00:52.706
Dear, we love your mountains.

00:00:55.726 --> 00:01:00.663
Drava, Sava, keep on flowing,

00:01:02.552 --> 00:01:06.830
Danube, do not lose your vigour,

00:01:09.471 --> 00:01:13.418
Deep blue sea, tell the world,

00:01:16.301 --> 00:01:21.268
That a Croat loves his homeland.

00:01:23.557 --> 00:01:28.569
Whilst his fields are kissed by sunshine,

00:01:30.173 --> 00:01:34.916
Whilst his oaks are whipped by wild winds,

00:01:37.029 --> 00:01:42.000
Whilst his dear ones go to heaven,

00:01:43.600 --> 00:01:48.806
Whilst his live heart beats.

00:01:54.000 --> 00:02:00.696
I kindly ask you for a minute of silence for all the dead, missing, the veterans, pregnant women, and unborn children.

00:02:11.851 --> 00:02:16.880
Eternal rest grant unto them, O Lord... (and let perpetual light shine upon them.)

00:02:16.880 --> 00:02:18.463
May they rest in peace.

00:02:18.463 --> 00:02:21.741
Dear ladies and gentlemen, good day. Praised be Jesus and Mary. 

00:02:22.241 --> 00:02:30.382
Welcome to the event that the Association"Croatia for Life" has been waiting for five years – the opening of the Croatian Rose monument. 

00:02:30.915 --> 00:02:37.588
First of all, I want to thank Juraj Elez and professor Renata Somrak for the dignified performance of the Croatian national anthem.

00:02:38.171 --> 00:02:45.545
I will use the opportunity to greet and thank for his arrival, on behalf of the Archbishop of Đakovo-Osijek, Msgr. Đuro Hranić, 

00:02:45.906 --> 00:02:50.379
the auxiliary bishop of the Archdiocese of Đakovo-Osijek, Msgr. Ivan Ćurić, 

00:02:51.444 --> 00:02:54.732
Bishop of Sisak, Msgr. Vlado Košić, 

00:02:54.732 --> 00:03:02.734
Prefect of Vukovar-Srijem County, Damir Dekanić, and associates, as well as the Mayor of Vukovar, Ivan Penava.

00:03:03.702 --> 00:03:08.449
I am glad that the president of the Association "Croatia for Life", Ante Čaljkušić, is among us today,

00:03:08.727 --> 00:03:18.160
and I am honored to greet the author of the monument, academic sculptor Lovre Jakšić, whose bust of Jean-Michel Nicolier already adorns the center of Vukovar. 

00:03:18.957 --> 00:03:27.339
It is a special pleasure for me to welcome Ružica’s daughter Adnana, who traveled from Germany to attend this event.

00:03:28.394 --> 00:03:33.033
I have already mentioned that the Association"Croatia for Life" has been waiting for this event for five years.

00:03:33.366 --> 00:03:38.450
Providence wanted it to be just before the 30th anniversary of the fall of the city of Vukovar, 

00:03:38.811 --> 00:03:44.062
and the opening date itself on the first anniversary of the death of Ružica’s husband Davor. 

00:03:44.903 --> 00:03:51.551
Ružica Markobašić and her unborn son Antun were victims of a brutal murder in Ovčara.

00:03:52.642 --> 00:03:59.873
We stand in front of this monument here as a sign of lasting memory and gratitude for the sacrifice of Ružica and her son,

00:04:00.627 --> 00:04:08.549
but also for all pregnant women, unborn children and all those who laid down their lives believing in Christ and for the freedom of Croatia. 

00:04:09.549 --> 00:04:19.097
We believe and pray that they enjoy eternal life with the Lord, that their sacrifice was not in vain, and that such crimes will never happen again. 

00:04:22.277 --> 00:04:26.763
The main coordinator of the Croatian Rose monument project is Lidija Dugan, 

00:04:26.763 --> 00:04:33.904
who will explain to us what has happened in the past five years and how it has come to this moment of the monument’s ceremonial opening.

00:04:34.015 --> 00:04:34.904
Lidija, the floor is yours.

00:04:42.340 --> 00:04:46.025
Praised be Jesus and Mary, welcome everyone. It’s nice to see you all.

00:04:46.358 --> 00:04:51.193
 I would like to tell you a little about how this idea came about 

00:04:51.360 --> 00:04:58.028
and how this big project that our Association has been working on for the last five years came to fruition.

00:04:58.600 --> 00:05:06.386
Namely, the Association ''Croatia for Life'' is an association that fights for the protection of unborn life from conception to natural death, 

00:05:06.719 --> 00:05:13.386
and we are also the 40 Days for Life initiative that is active in 35 cities throughout our beloved country. 

00:05:14.108 --> 00:05:21.241
We keep vigil like this in front of hospitals and pray for an end to abortion, that is, for the preservation of every unborn life. 

00:05:22.263 --> 00:05:28.036
In 2015, when our initiative started with a prayer here in front of our hospital in Vukovar,

00:05:28.536 --> 00:05:36.000
our big national meeting, where all members from Croatia gathered, took place in Vukovar in May.

00:05:37.289 --> 00:05:41.190
During the tour of the city and all war-stricken places,

00:05:41.742 --> 00:05:44.906
 the retired colonel of the Croatian army, Antun Dugan,

00:05:45.017 --> 00:05:51.818
guided us around all the strategic places that were important for Croatia and Vukovar during the Homeland War. 

00:05:52.040 --> 00:05:57.640
That’s how we got to Ovčara, where he told us the story of Ružica Markobašić, 

00:05:57.640 --> 00:06:02.307
saying that 200 bushes were planted for all those who died in that place, 

00:06:03.378 --> 00:06:10.145
but that there was one missing that would mark her son Antun, the unborn child who died there. 

00:06:11.622 --> 00:06:21.295
As we are an Association that fights for the protection of unborn life, we decided that it would be very nice if we could do something for that unborn Antun. 

00:06:23.520 --> 00:06:29.080
We then tried in various ways how to pay homage to his victim.

00:06:29.633 --> 00:06:39.758
However, some doors were not open to us, some answers were not satisfactory to us, and we simply, apart from that human way, began to pray a lot that the Lord 

00:06:39.758 --> 00:06:43.759
would enlighten us and we would see what we could do. 

00:06:44.259 --> 00:06:50.427
That’s how we got the idea and motivation to make a monument that would adorn this very place.

00:06:50.705 --> 00:06:56.401
In fact, the place where we usually stand and watch in front of the hospital for 40 days. 

00:06:56.920 --> 00:07:00.451
We started thinking about what that monument would look like. 

00:07:00.451 --> 00:07:10.920
Somehow, my original idea was that it should not be in bronze, but that it should be beautiful, in stone, white, immortal, magnificent, and that it should actually 

00:07:11.087 --> 00:07:17.088
depict the moment of victory and the moment of Ružica’s entry into the eternal kingdom.

00:07:17.400 --> 00:07:20.178
That’s what we got with this monument. 

00:07:20.178 --> 00:07:27.152
We also found an author who would do it for us, and that is our sculptor Lovre Jakšić from the island of Brač. 

00:07:27.152 --> 00:07:30.680
Since he also made the monument of Jean-Michel that adorns the city center, 

00:07:30.902 --> 00:07:36.181
we concluded that he would be perfect for doing both this job and task we have for him.

00:07:36.966 --> 00:07:42.974
There were many obstacles, a lot of pain, a lot of tears, a lot of things we went through. 

00:07:43.307 --> 00:07:46.947
But here we are, happy that we finally got to see this wonderful day. 

00:07:47.336 --> 00:07:55.765
What I would like to point out is that this monument would not have been possible without some people who are very important to us. 

00:07:56.458 --> 00:08:05.431
These are our architect, Damir Moskalj, our sculptor, Lovre Jakšić, president of the Association, Ante Čaljkušić, who actually came up with the idea 

00:08:05.431 --> 00:08:13.599
to pay tribute to this victim, and these are all the people who participated so that this place would be openhere 

00:08:14.676 --> 00:08:24.366
Also, I would like to especially thank our dear mayor, Ivan Penava, who two or three years ago, when we came to him with this idea, supported us and said that he would 

00:08:25.327 --> 00:08:30.123
and said that he would do everything in his power to help us make it happen. 

00:08:30.429 --> 00:08:35.096
We envision this place as a place of victory.

00:08:35.318 --> 00:08:41.097
We envision this place as a place of healing, 

00:08:41.097 --> 00:08:47.015
so that some day all mothers who may have experienced an abortion, 

00:08:47.348 --> 00:08:55.961
whether they chose to do it themselves, unfortunately, or whether they experienced miscarriage, loss of a child or family members who lost a pregnant woman in the war, 

00:08:57.363 --> 00:09:03.349
can come to it. They can come here, they can look at Ružica, and they can simply feel peace in their heart. 

00:09:03.910 --> 00:09:07.249
God’s providence is truly magnificent, 

00:09:07.249 --> 00:09:17.640
When we agreed with the mayor the day which would actually be important and which would serve as the opening of the memorial, he chose it to be November 16, exactly 2 days before the Column of Remembrance.

00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:20.224
 exactly 2 days before the Column of Remembrance.

00:09:20.224 --> 00:09:28.448
November 16 ended up being the day when we mark one year since the death of Mr. Davor Markobašić, 

00:09:29.528 --> 00:09:36.440
who was the husband of Ružica Markobašić and who was the father of our little unborn Antun. 

00:09:36.607 --> 00:09:46.164
November 16 today is Tuesday when the Church celebrates the day of the week dedicated to St. Anthony, and the little one’s name was Antun. 

00:09:46.790 --> 00:09:55.557
This day is also important because our generals, Ante Gotovina and others, were released on November 16, 2012. 

00:09:56.721 --> 00:10:00.219
So we see the finger of God in all this. 

00:10:00.219 --> 00:10:08.026
We would like to thank everyone who participated in any way, and the person I really especially want to greet, to whom I want to thank,

00:10:08.910 --> 00:10:19.963
is our very good friend, Mr. Zlatko Zaoborni, who participated in everything, coordinated everything, listened to our instructions, suggested things 

00:10:20.840 --> 00:10:22.846
in order to make this monument come to life. 

00:10:23.040 --> 00:10:30.000
. I thank you once again on behalf of our Association for coming and God bless you. Thank you very much.

00:10:36.939 --> 00:10:42.350
Many thanks to Lidija Dugan. Now I kindly ask Mayor Ivan Penava to address us with a few words.

00:10:44.553 --> 00:10:46.440
Good day to all. 

00:10:46.940 --> 00:10:51.608
I greet everyone according to the order that our moderator used. 

00:10:51.608 --> 00:10:55.914
Lidija also, and I thank her for it, thanked and greeted 

00:10:58.303 --> 00:11:00.692
all the key people in this project. 

00:11:01.280 --> 00:11:07.547
I would also like to greet the Members of Parliament who are here with us today. 

00:11:07.547 --> 00:11:14.243
Mrs. Marijana Petir, Ante Prkačin and Ćipo Stipe Mlinarić. 

00:11:17.632 --> 00:11:22.410
Lidija has said everything. I really don’t need to add anything. 

00:11:23.954 --> 00:11:27.943
I want to thank you all for your contribution, 

00:11:28.497 --> 00:11:32.969
and indeed there are many of you who have contributed to today’s event. 

00:11:33.929 --> 00:11:41.252
I’m glad. Lidia’s words exude a certain peace and that’s how it should be. 

00:11:42.150 --> 00:11:53.106
I am currently in an exclusive phase of restlessness because of the previous press conference and this 30th anniversary and all that load of unresolved issues. 

00:11:53.106 --> 00:11:57.551
I think you recognize and know what I’m talking about.

00:11:58.491 --> 00:12:04.682
I was impressed by one thought in the invitation and I will repeat it. . I will actually mention only that.

00:12:05.333 --> 00:12:07.818
A conclusion with which I agree. 

00:12:07.818 --> 00:12:21.710
Namely, that because of bad stories, vile stories about the late Davor Markobašić himself, Ružica very likely ended up in this way. 

00:12:22.755 --> 00:12:31.580
And that is a story that is repeated continuously to our people, to individuals among us, to our city. 

00:12:32.163 --> 00:12:39.477
That we are always some radicals, extremists, Nazis, idiots.

00:12:39.477 --> 00:12:47.617
In fact, they are trying to take away our human form in some way, so that we can be written off more easily, which, unfortunately, is 

00:12:47.617 --> 00:12:57.063
best evidenced by this monument in the form of Ružica and the tragedy of her unborn son Antun. 

00:12:58.700 --> 00:13:05.866
I invite you to calmly be aware that this is the case, not to stop 

00:13:06.960 --> 00:13:17.779
with peace in ourselves and not to agree that the Danube continues to flow, and not to forget these things and to solve these things. 

00:13:18.474 --> 00:13:24.000
Because we still have a lot of tasks ahead of us that we have to solve. 

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:30.000
I would like it to be in peace and in the spirit as Lidija said. Thank you all.

00:13:36.395 --> 00:13:39.817
Thank you very much, mayor. It’s time for three recitals. 

00:13:39.817 --> 00:13:43.129
The first "Our Little Lady" by Antun Gustav Matoš

00:13:43.268 --> 00:13:48.880
 will be performed by student Eva Šibalić, the child of a large family whose grandfather was a  colonel in the Croatian Army.

00:13:49.811 --> 00:13:53.270
Matoš’s "Consolationin Hair" will be interpreted by Marin Miletić, 

00:13:53.631 --> 00:13:56.742
, a man who recently lost his beloved wife,

00:13:56.742 --> 00:14:01.187
 and who showed us the power of prayer and faith in God by his example.

00:14:01.576 --> 00:14:09.478
"Letter to my unborn child", which was written by a young Slovenian teacher who was eight months pregnant the night before her execution execution on Bleiburg, 

00:14:10.935 --> 00:14:17.338
will be read by Katarina Seider, a member of the choir of St. Cecilia of the Vukovar parish of Saints Philip and James. 

00:14:17.838 --> 00:14:21.116
All three recitals will be accompanied by Ivana Huk on the violin.

00:14:58.319 --> 00:15:01.028
There is a little lady Mary,

00:15:01.568 --> 00:15:04.998
who grows fonder to me as she gets older.

00:15:05.771 --> 00:15:09.101
Because she was the first who heavily gave birth to me, 

00:15:09.101 --> 00:15:11.684
lead me holding my weak little hand.

00:15:12.922 --> 00:15:15.910
She was the first one on this world to love me,

00:15:15.910 --> 00:15:19.355
the first who prayed to Lord for me.

00:15:19.984 --> 00:15:21.474
She bath me with a tear, 

00:15:21.891 --> 00:15:23.130
God bless her. 

00:15:23.783 --> 00:15:27.242
May angel give her a tear for each tear. 

00:15:27.464 --> 00:15:30.881
She breastfed me with the milk of her love, 

00:15:31.442 --> 00:15:34.680
she thought me this lovely language,

00:15:35.190 --> 00:15:38.118
, in which then I will sweetly talk endearly, 

00:15:38.118 --> 00:15:42.000
while I might drop dead behind a fence.

00:15:42.658 --> 00:15:45.789
Only you I love, dear nation. 

00:15:46.039 --> 00:15:48.873
Only you I serve, oh, Croatia. 

00:15:49.486 --> 00:15:50.599
Who art the soul, 

00:15:51.016 --> 00:15:51.780
language,

00:15:52.134 --> 00:15:52.682
mother,

00:15:53.210 --> 00:15:54.113
and not a sign,

00:15:54.835 --> 00:15:55.710
For you I live, 

00:15:56.373 --> 00:15:57.203
only for you.

00:15:57.676 --> 00:15:58.815
Amen!

00:17:10.165 --> 00:17:13.056
Antun Gustav Matoš

00:17:13.877 --> 00:17:15.365
Solace of hair.

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:19.689
I watched you last night. 

00:17:20.189 --> 00:17:21.134
Asleep.

00:17:22.248 --> 00:17:23.112
Sad.

00:17:24.112 --> 00:17:24.986
You were dead.

00:17:26.321 --> 00:17:29.684
In the fatal hall, in the flower idyl. 

00:17:30.267 --> 00:17:33.168
On the high deathbed, in the candle lit agony, 

00:17:33.999 --> 00:17:34.830
resolved 

00:17:35.708 --> 00:17:37.753
to give you my life

00:17:38.530 --> 00:17:39.724
 as sacrifice.

00:17:41.438 --> 00:17:42.596
I did not cry. 

00:17:42.596 --> 00:17:43.566
I did not.

00:17:44.321 --> 00:17:51.688
Astonished I stood in the fatal hall, full of grand death, in doubt that dark, clear, eyes are the ones 

00:17:53.509 --> 00:17:57.025
from where better life shined for me.

00:17:58.874 --> 00:18:00.000
Everything,

00:18:00.849 --> 00:18:02.420
but everything is dead: 

00:18:02.781 --> 00:18:04.365
eyes, 

00:18:04.365 --> 00:18:05.282
breath 

00:18:06.409 --> 00:18:07.536
and hands,

00:18:09.036 --> 00:18:12.000
everything I wanted to bring to life with desperation 

00:18:12.167 --> 00:18:15.445
in a blind horror and in the passion of torment. 

00:18:17.140 --> 00:18:18.592
In the fatal hall, 

00:18:19.120 --> 00:18:21.226
in thoughts of grey.

00:18:21.671 --> 00:18:22.445
Only 

00:18:23.084 --> 00:18:24.386
your hair 

00:18:25.470 --> 00:18:27.011
was still alive 

00:18:28.512 --> 00:18:29.735
so it told me: 

00:18:30.352 --> 00:18:31.497
''Be still! 

00:18:32.325 --> 00:18:34.403
 In death one dreams.''

00:19:04.301 --> 00:19:08.548
A few more hours until the end of my life. 

00:19:08.548 --> 00:19:09.048
Oh, God, 

00:19:09.968 --> 00:19:12.861
oh, You sorrowful Mother of God, my Mother, 

00:19:13.805 --> 00:19:16.166
You know that I die innocent,

00:19:16.638 --> 00:19:18.638
 as Your innocent Son died... 

00:19:21.194 --> 00:19:23.750
Oh, my child, my gentle angel,

00:19:25.081 --> 00:19:28.023
how I would love to see the features of your face, 

00:19:28.356 --> 00:19:30.217
the gentle pearls of your eyes. 

00:19:31.284 --> 00:19:35.852
I will never see your blossoming smile to make me happy, 

00:19:37.468 --> 00:19:40.779
, oh, my child, my tender flower! 

00:19:41.570 --> 00:19:44.500
I will never see your white hands,

00:19:44.722 --> 00:19:48.917
you will never stretch them out to return my sweet embrace. 

00:19:50.143 --> 00:19:53.620
I will never be able to press you to my heart, 

00:19:54.000 --> 00:19:56.445
even though you are so close to it. 

00:19:57.011 --> 00:19:59.040
Never, my child! 

00:20:00.247 --> 00:20:03.760
Somewhere in the embrace of the forest will be our home, 

00:20:04.278 --> 00:20:07.019
which will be decorated with spring flowers. 

00:20:07.325 --> 00:20:08.131
 My mouth

00:20:09.015 --> 00:20:12.177
will not be able to sing a song over your cradle, 

00:20:12.538 --> 00:20:16.233
and your cradle will be me alone, 

00:20:16.817 --> 00:20:19.846
although so cold and hardened. 

00:20:21.636 --> 00:20:25.565
The branches above us will sing to you and rustle a beloved lullaby. 

00:20:27.249 --> 00:20:30.000
Oh, just sleep peacefully, my child, 

00:20:30.641 --> 00:20:33.116
you are so close to my loving heart.

00:20:34.616 --> 00:20:35.499
And yet, 

00:20:36.071 --> 00:20:40.311
it cannot tear you out of the embrace of death that awaits you too. 

00:20:41.315 --> 00:20:42.819
Just sleep peacefully, 

00:20:43.533 --> 00:20:46.331
because you have no idea what’s coming. 

00:20:46.859 --> 00:20:50.165
You will die with me, and I will die with you. 

00:20:51.153 --> 00:20:53.586
And then, when the fight is over, 

00:20:53.753 --> 00:20:56.003
we will go to God together... 

00:20:56.703 --> 00:21:05.849
When I felt you under my heart for the first time and felt your restlessness, , I already dreamed that for the first time I would bring you close to God to be spattered 

00:21:05.849 --> 00:21:07.223
with baptismal water

00:21:08.342 --> 00:21:11.378
 –you will be spattered soon by my blood.

00:21:12.000 --> 00:21:15.818
You will be baptized with the beloved blood of your own mother. 

00:21:17.513 --> 00:21:21.123
Soon, my body will be a gifted ciborium. 

00:21:22.231 --> 00:21:25.673
You, on the other hand, my child, the Host in it. 

00:21:26.853 --> 00:21:33.451
The Creator will take the Host of your being in his loving hands and place it in His Divine Heart. 

00:21:35.327 --> 00:21:39.565
There I will see you for the first time, there I will see your face. 

00:21:40.449 --> 00:21:45.612
There you will see your mother and for the first time you will call out to me: 

00:21:46.450 --> 00:21:47.288
"Oh, mom!" 

00:21:48.742 --> 00:21:51.780
Look, my child, the morning is coming. 

00:21:52.475 --> 00:21:55.559
 For us, the last morning of suffering. 

00:21:56.066 --> 00:21:59.268
The morning will dawn again, , but without tears. 

00:22:00.000 --> 00:22:01.483
It will dawn with God. 

00:22:02.200 --> 00:22:05.390
Just sleep peacefully, your mother is watching over you. 

00:22:06.724 --> 00:22:10.591
Look, the red dawn announces that the day is waking up... 

00:22:11.147 --> 00:22:13.853
and the last stars are extinguished in it. 

00:22:14.489 --> 00:22:20.404
The clock on the tower announces the morning that will take us on our last journey... 

00:22:21.432 --> 00:22:23.016
but I won’t be alone... 

00:22:23.725 --> 00:22:26.823
you will be with me, my child. 

00:22:28.061 --> 00:22:33.106
And Mary, like then with her Son on Calvary, will go with us.

00:22:33.740 --> 00:22:39.625
In our last breaths, they will stand by us and take us to the Eternal Home of Joy.

00:22:41.551 --> 00:22:44.060
No one will disturb our happiness anymore.

00:22:45.008 --> 00:22:45.956
We will be immersed 

00:22:46.836 --> 00:22:47.716
in the Eternal God, 

00:22:48.437 --> 00:22:49.964
His eternal peace. 

00:22:51.282 --> 00:22:53.600
My baby, just sleep. 

00:22:54.628 --> 00:22:55.778
Mary is with us. 

00:22:56.751 --> 00:22:57.650
Look... 

00:22:58.234 --> 00:22:59.096
they’re coming... 

00:22:59.462 --> 00:23:01.273
they’re coming... 

00:23:41.310 --> 00:23:44.555
Many thanks to Eva, Marin, Katarina and Ivana. 

00:23:45.055 --> 00:23:47.722
They left a piece of their soul in their interpretations.

00:23:48.493 --> 00:23:52.404
It is time for the blessing of the monument and those present as well as the service of the Word.

00:23:52.626 --> 00:23:56.988
I kindly ask the auxiliary bishop of the Archdiocese of Đakovo-Osijek, Mons. Ivan Ćurić, for his blessing.

00:24:16.578 --> 00:24:20.470
In the name of the Father, the Son and the Holy Spirit. (Amen.)

00:24:20.470 --> 00:24:22.470
Peace be with you. (And with your spirit.)

00:24:23.456 --> 00:24:24.998
Let us sing the antiphon: 

00:24:25.874 --> 00:24:30.195
Send forth your spirit, O Lord, and renew the peace of the earth.
 

00:24:31.334 --> 00:24:38.058
(Send forth your spirit, O Lord,

00:24:43.809 --> 00:24:49.691
 and renew the peace of the earth!)

00:24:54.706 --> 00:24:57.332
Praise the Lord, my soul.

00:24:57.665 --> 00:25:00.332
Lord my God, you are very great. 

00:25:00.832 --> 00:25:03.221
How many are your works, Lord! 

00:25:03.732 --> 00:25:05.549
The earth is full of your creatures. 

00:25:06.248 --> 00:25:14.810
When you hide your face, they are terrified; when you take away their breath, they die and return to the dust.

00:25:15.489 --> 00:25:21.058
When you send your Spirit, they are created,and you renew the face of the ground.

00:25:23.225 --> 00:25:29.239
Glory be to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit (as it was in the beginning, is now, and ever shall be, world without end. Amen.)

00:25:33.598 --> 00:25:35.318
Let us sing the antiphon: 

00:25:35.485 --> 00:25:39.347
I praise you, I praise you because I am fearfully and wonderfully made

00:25:41.236 --> 00:25:46.734
(I praise you, I praise you because I am fearfully and wonderfully made).

00:25:56.708 --> 00:26:00.227
You have searched me, Lord,and you know me. 

00:26:00.581 --> 00:26:02.430
You are familiar with all my ways. 

00:26:03.284 --> 00:26:05.388
For you created my inmost being;

00:26:05.749 --> 00:26:07.805
you knit me together in my mother’s womb

00:26:08.478 --> 00:26:10.985
I praise you because I am fearfully and wonderfully made;

00:26:11.830 --> 00:26:13.703
your works are wonderful,I know that full well.

00:26:14.200 --> 00:26:16.367
My frame was not hidden from you when 

00:26:17.227 --> 00:26:23.672
I was made in the secret place,when I was woven together in the depths of the earth.

00:26:26.079 --> 00:26:32.320
Glory be to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit (as it was in the beginning, is now, and ever shall be, world without end. Amen.)

00:26:36.557 --> 00:26:39.071
Dear Father Bishop Vlado, 

00:26:39.599 --> 00:26:41.599
dear Franciscan fathers, 

00:26:41.738 --> 00:26:44.211
all dear priest brothers and religious sisters. 

00:26:46.401 --> 00:26:48.285
Honorable Members of Parliament, 

00:26:49.730 --> 00:26:55.611
Mr. Prefect, Mr. Mayor, and all representatives of social life, 

00:26:56.667 --> 00:27:01.584
respected doctors, representatives of this National Memorial Hospital in Vukovar, 

00:27:03.353 --> 00:27:05.122
all dear brothers and sisters,

00:27:05.455 --> 00:27:10.123
 and in a special way dear members of the Association "Croatia for Life",

00:27:10.909 --> 00:27:17.752
led by the president, Mr. Ante Čaljkušić, and in this eastern part of our homeland, 

00:27:18.000 --> 00:27:25.085
as we see, by the initiator of this memorial work, Mrs. Lidija Dugan.

00:27:26.472 --> 00:27:34.944
We listened and partly pronounced the biblical words from the 104th and 139th psalms together. 

00:27:36.504 --> 00:27:42.259
They contain a small psalmody, a hymn to God the creator. 

00:27:44.277 --> 00:27:55.131
And wherever we turn in depth, in height, on all sides of our world and universe, we recognize and discover God’s creatures. 

00:27:56.599 --> 00:28:05.097
In this light of faith and Christian spirituality, my dear people, rests the original dignity of everything that exists.

00:28:06.879 --> 00:28:08.661
 And not only at the beginning. 

00:28:08.855 --> 00:28:11.606
. God is the restorer of life by the power of his spirit. 

00:28:12.253 --> 00:28:14.873
Everything can be restored by its power. 

00:28:15.901 --> 00:28:24.264
And in the most excellent way, as a reflection of God’s existence, in His image, there is also a living man. 

00:28:26.181 --> 00:28:33.321
That is why this occasion strengthens us in the Christian teaching that human life is sacred. 

00:28:34.882 --> 00:28:44.000
Because from the very beginning it requires the Creator’s action and remains permanently connected to the creator, its only purpose

00:28:45.333 --> 00:28:49.111
God is the only master of life from beginning to end. 

00:28:49.417 --> 00:28:57.641
No one, under any circumstances, can claim the right to directly kill an innocent human creature of God.

00:29:01.490 --> 00:29:05.339
At the time of the Homeland War in 1994, 

00:29:05.617 --> 00:29:10.368
Saint Pope John Paul II told the church and the whole world: 

00:29:10.701 --> 00:29:19.147
"We are all called to do what is possible in order to remove from human society not only the horror of war,

00:29:19.677 --> 00:29:29.304
 but also any threat to human rights starting from the indisputable right to life that a human person has from conception. 

00:29:31.305 --> 00:29:39.689
In extinguishing the right to life, even if only of one human being, is contained", says the Holy Pope, 

00:29:40.384 --> 00:29:43.614
"the germ of the ultimate violence of war."

00:29:45.441 --> 00:29:53.325
And precisely in the summer of 1991, when war sufferings began throughout our homeland, and especially in this region of Vukovar, 

00:29:54.651 --> 00:30:03.090
the same pope, having in front of him numerous tragedies caused by wars in our modern times, would state as follows: 

00:30:04.113 --> 00:30:11.749
"To this cemetery of the victims of human cruelty of the 20th century another large cemetery is added.

00:30:12.000 --> 00:30:13.778
Cemetery of the unborn. 

00:30:14.403 --> 00:30:19.862
The cemetery of the helpless whose face not even their own mother has met. 

00:30:21.086 --> 00:30:31.264
And they already had that life, they were already conceived, they were developing under the heart of their mothers without suspecting the danger of death."

00:30:31.758 --> 00:30:40.226
There is so much, my dear brothers and sisters, that is holy, dignified, gentle and sensitive, 

00:30:40.559 --> 00:30:48.000
unfortunately, often unprotected and endangered, displayed in this monument to the pregnant woman. 

00:30:49.417 --> 00:30:56.821
Remembering the cruelly slaughtered pregnant Ružica Markobašić and her unborn child Antun.

00:30:58.413 --> 00:30:59.533
An event that, 

00:30:59.839 --> 00:31:12.825
with its horror, only added to the pot of tragic suffering and suffering endured 30 years ago here in the city of Vukovar, in Ovčara and throughout our Croatia. 

00:31:15.381 --> 00:31:24.745
This monument is also a memorial to all the pregnant women who died in the war, women in, as we say, a blessed state,

00:31:24.745 --> 00:31:31.941
 in whose sufferings we always hear the double cry of both the mother and the unborn child.

00:31:32.745 --> 00:31:39.189
That is why we would like to thank the Association"Croatia for Life 

00:31:39.300 --> 00:31:43.745
for reminding us of this with this accomplished initiative. 

00:31:45.597 --> 00:31:54.000
That is why today in a special way in this place we want to surrender human life to divine providence,

00:31:54.222 --> 00:32:00.000
 and especially the life of unborn children in our homeland and around the world. 

00:32:00.537 --> 00:32:09.215
Because life has an unrepeatable dignity, all the more so as each person is called to participate in God’s life.

00:32:11.021 --> 00:32:16.578
Always living the joy of the truth that the apostle John testifies to us: 

00:32:16.578 --> 00:32:23.079
"See what great love the Father has lavished on us, that we should be called children of God! And that is what we are!" 

00:32:25.718 --> 00:32:33.886
That is why we will pray the Lord’s prayer, in which Bishop Vlado will lead us in the blessing.

00:32:40.763 --> 00:32:50.585
Let’s say our prayer to the Heavenly Father for the blessing of this statue, but also for the blessing of all mothers, pregnant women, and conceived children.

00:32:54.001 --> 00:32:57.417
Our Father… who art in heaven, hallowed be Thy name; 

00:32:57.417 --> 00:33:00.169
Invited so many times to join 40 Days for Life, with the Association "Croatia for 

00:33:00.169 --> 00:33:02.060
Thy kingdom come; 

00:33:02.366 --> 00:33:03.366
Thy will be done 

00:33:04.173 --> 00:33:05.786
on earth as it is in heaven. 

00:33:07.035 --> 00:33:15.266
Give us this day our daily bread; and forgive us our trespasses as we forgive those who trespass against us; 

00:33:15.844 --> 00:33:19.951
and lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.

00:33:20.090 --> 00:33:20.590
Let us pray. 

00:33:21.314 --> 00:33:27.762
God, originator and protector of human life, graciously receive and answer our prayers 

00:33:28.715 --> 00:33:33.836
for the late Ružica and all mothers murdered while carrying their unborn children under their hearts. 

00:33:36.476 --> 00:33:45.374
Accept them and their murdered children with them with your resurrection so that they can rejoice in the fullness of life in you, who lives and reigns forever and ever. Amen.

00:33:49.388 --> 00:33:58.792
Invited so many times to join 40 Days for Life, with the Association "Croatia for Life.

00:34:01.098 --> 00:34:03.932
let us turn to our heavenly Mother in prayer. 

00:34:04.845 --> 00:34:12.343
We entrust to your Immaculate Heart, Virgin Mary, every child conceived, but not yet born. 

00:34:12.621 --> 00:34:18.622
Save its life, and ask all parents for peace and love for it. 

00:34:20.225 --> 00:34:29.747
Turn your gaze also to the wretched who struggle with the adversities of life, to men and women victims of mindless violence,

00:34:30.736 --> 00:34:37.726
to the old and sick, all scarred by indifference and false sympathy. 

00:34:39.401 --> 00:34:48.244
Make that all who believe in your Son, ready and with love, spread the Gospel of life to the people of our time.

00:34:49.216 --> 00:34:51.451
The Lord be with you. (And with your spirit.)

00:34:52.020 --> 00:34:54.812
Let the name of the Lord be praised. (Both now and forevermore.)

00:34:56.400 --> 00:35:02.711
May the blessing of Almighty God, Father, Son, and the Holy Spirit descend upon us. (Amen.)

00:35:49.021 --> 00:35:56.098
This monument also stands here for all pregnant women and their children who died in the wars on Croatian territory. 

00:35:56.292 --> 00:36:03.821
The fight for pregnant women, their families and unborn children and for building a culture of life is especially close to the heart of the Association Croatia for Life.

00:36:07.306 --> 00:36:10.624
The President of the Association, Ante Čaljkušić, will now address us with a few words.

00:36:17.320 --> 00:36:18.000
Praised be Jesus and Mary. 

00:36:19.751 --> 00:36:20.557
Good afternoon. 

00:36:22.428 --> 00:36:24.299
Dear brothers, dear sisters,

00:36:25.725 --> 00:36:26.734
a lot has been said. 

00:36:28.299 --> 00:36:29.864
I wish you all

00:36:31.281 --> 00:36:33.761
a sense of peace. 

00:36:35.279 --> 00:36:36.797
A feeling of tenderness. 

00:36:38.051 --> 00:36:42.000
And let these emotions follow you when you go home.

00:36:45.285 --> 00:36:49.737
And to convey what you experienced in this place of peace and tranquility. 

00:36:54.302 --> 00:36:58.867
 I want to responsibly share something with you. 

00:36:59.833 --> 00:37:00.799
My thought. 

00:37:03.360 --> 00:37:13.735
Brothers and sisters, there is no pandemic and no earthquake that can be compared to the evil of killing an unborn child and a pregnant woman. 

00:37:21.388 --> 00:37:22.178
No!

00:37:23.123 --> 00:37:30.885
 Because actually that act is an earthquake of the human soul and a disease of the human spirit. 

00:37:33.469 --> 00:37:40.665
And the only one who can cure and heal our wounds is the Lord Jesus. 

00:37:45.138 --> 00:37:54.719
We have heard the verses, we have heard the words of encouragement, we have been blessed and now let us keep it in our hearts.

00:37:57.499 --> 00:38:04.752
Let us not reject all that we have received today from the Lord, through these people who have turned to you.

00:38:10.057 --> 00:38:11.500
Dear friends, 

00:38:12.972 --> 00:38:14.074
each of you individuallyis 

00:38:18.497 --> 00:38:22.170
called here to be the protector of another. 

00:38:27.088 --> 00:38:36.327
When it comes to life, when it comes to, I don’t know what, to be its protector and to be called to give of yourself, even when it hurts and when it’s difficult. 

00:38:40.789 --> 00:38:47.196
Just so that the other would be better, be well. 

00:38:47.696 --> 00:38:56.200
Dear politicians, representatives, my friends, Ivan, Marijana, Marin, all present, 

00:38:58.617 --> 00:39:03.374
you are public representatives of born and unborn Croats.

00:39:06.152 --> 00:39:17.650
My dear friends, bishops Ivan and Vlado, you are especially called to serve the born and unborn children of God. 

00:39:23.346 --> 00:39:24.179
All of us. 

00:39:25.517 --> 00:39:26.049
Why?

00:39:26.660 --> 00:39:32.411
Because each of us is magnificent, each of us is unique in the history of mankind.

00:39:36.349 --> 00:39:40.287
Ante Čaljkušić or sculptor Lovre Jakšić or bishop Vlado Košić will never be repeated.

00:39:44.843 --> 00:39:46.538
Never anyone of you here. 

00:39:47.872 --> 00:39:51.466
We are precious for that uniqueness, 

00:39:52.355 --> 00:39:59.300
and so is our friend and sister in Christ Ružica Markobašić

00:40:00.468 --> 00:40:08.971
Markobašić and her unborn son Antun, together with the father and husband 

00:40:09.721 --> 00:40:14.365
who passed away a year ago, our dear Davor. 

00:40:17.449 --> 00:40:24.888
What we did was the least we could do for this family 

00:40:26.305 --> 00:40:31.958
and for all other families whose pregnant women died on Croatian territories. 

00:40:35.582 --> 00:40:39.424
And what we can do more for the present

00:40:40.313 --> 00:40:48.819
 and for the future is to protect, advocate and defend the dignity of every human being in every place from their conception to their natural death. 

00:40:58.827 --> 00:41:05.056
And we will all see how much Croatian society will change, 

00:41:07.890 --> 00:41:09.890
how much we will love each other. 

00:41:11.923 --> 00:41:19.513
Despite our differences, despite various political affiliations, despite different attitudes, one thing connects us. 

00:41:20.430 --> 00:41:21.477
One thing connects us.

00:41:22.970 --> 00:41:26.964
 And that is that each of us was conceived. 

00:41:30.755 --> 00:41:31.907
Even Jesus Christ, 

00:41:33.241 --> 00:41:44.904
an unborn child, stayed in love under the heart of His mother Mary for 9 months, 

00:41:45.293 --> 00:41:49.066
precisely so that He would be similar to us. 

00:41:51.597 --> 00:42:01.074
Let’s remember this well. Let’s remember these words well, because these words that are spoken now

00:42:02.102 --> 00:42:03.205
 are not from me 

00:42:04.789 --> 00:42:07.956
but from the Holy Spirit. 

00:42:08.706 --> 00:42:12.535
And these words that you have heard are blessings, 

00:42:15.508 --> 00:42:20.367
blessings and only blessings

00:42:20.589 --> 00:42:22.395
 in abundance. 

00:42:25.729 --> 00:42:26.343
Finally,

00:42:29.196 --> 00:42:35.660
I thank my friend Davoru 

00:42:35.854 --> 00:42:44.300
and my friend Lovre Jakšić for their patience, who worked with us for 5 years to make this happen. 

00:42:44.522 --> 00:42:53.024
And one day there will be maybe a booklet, so you will hear a little of this human intrigue. God’s blessing, all the best and let’s rejoice!

00:43:00.504 --> 00:43:07.984
Many thanks to Ante Čaljkušić. A big thank you to all of you for being a part of this historic moment for the City of Vukovar, but also for the whole of Croatia. 

00:43:08.484 --> 00:43:14.374
We have finished the official part of the solemn opening of the monument. Now let us stay together in song and fellowship. 

00:43:15.112 --> 00:43:15.850
Thank you!

